I just dinged 52 last night, and was wondering about using evasive in normal experience groups.  I mostly duo with a 54 Cleric, and was thinking that I should be using this disc as often as I can to reduce the healing that the cleric has to dish out.  <br>
<br>
On the other hand, if I am continualy using the disc, it may not be up in case I do need it during a bad pull, etc...<br>
<br>
So I guess my question is wether I should be using this disc alot, or just save it for that one time every night I might absolutely need it.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukbam.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kbam</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/1/02 2:47:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2160.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Evasive and experience groups</span><hr size=1> When you go evasive you also hit the mob much less frequently so kills will take considerably longer.  I'd only use it in an emergency - like when you're praying for an extra couple seconds of life so the CH hits. <p><BR><B><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=17245>Kbam</a> - Mythic Legion Warlord</B><BR>
